Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:03.19,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As bright as a spark, with a penetratingly precise wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.19,0:00:04.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Once he gets started, you can't stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.81,0:00:06.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The case at the Spider House becomes more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.65,0:00:08.75,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran and Kazuha are in a dangerous situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.75,0:00:10.34,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:12.34,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.34,0:00:15.22,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.54,0:01:55.92,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We were called out to the Takeda home at Karakuri Pass in Tottori Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.92,0:01:59.97,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Heiji Hattori and Kazuha Tōyama got lost in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.97,0:02:02.26,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and met up with a foreigner by the name of Robert Taylor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:07.39,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We happened to pass by and find out that we had all been called out to the Takeda home
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.39,0:02:10.85,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}to solve the mystery of the curse at the "Spider House of Karakuri Pass".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.44,0:02:17.95,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}On the night we arrive, Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, the eldest son of the Takeda family,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.95,0:02:20.86,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}committed suicide on the second floor of the puppet warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.86,0:02:24.37,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Then someone suspicious appeared behind Kazuha...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:31.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[Mystery of the Spider House of Tottori (The Suspicion)]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.55,0:02:39.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! I found the mascot I was looking for!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:41.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was caught on the lid of the CD player...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.05,0:02:45.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.56,0:02:49.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s penlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.44,0:02:51.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.23,0:02:55.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.74,0:03:00.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, check this out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:03.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he's been hit on the back of the head with something!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:05.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:08.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the killer hit him, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:12.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The estimated time of death is about 9:00 PM,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.67,0:03:15.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,just around the time Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:20.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, he had already been called out by the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:25.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer met Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here and hit him on the head,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.01,0:03:28.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,knocking him unconscious, then strung him up by the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.97,0:03:32.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Then he{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}gled the body up in strings
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.23,0:03:35.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it look like the "Spider Mistress" curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.15,0:03:39.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:43.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How did the killer escape from the room after committing the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:50.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}dals and flashlight scattered on the floor also bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:54.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also strange that there's no dust on the shelves and floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The room was supposed to have been left alone for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:03:58.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:02.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that small window...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:06.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just about big enough for a kid to get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:10.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think it's important? Was it left open for a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.97,0:04:13.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I thought I heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:15.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran's voice just outside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.94,0:04:19.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Kazuha-{\i1}neechan{\i0}'s voice too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.02,0:04:23.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. Those two are probably in their room, fast asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:27.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:28.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:35.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's coming up the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.21,0:04:37.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Heavy feet... It's not Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.54,0:04:42.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd be coming here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:42.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:48.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet him in person and ask what the reason is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:52.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's the housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:53.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:58.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd be hungry, so I brought you some rice balls and tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.23,0:05:00.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this looks delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:04.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}? Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:06.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.53,0:05:08.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.62,0:05:16.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were friends with Misa Takeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the girl who died three years ago?{EOW 98}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:20.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We were nurses at the same hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:24.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the work was too hard for me, and I quit...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.30,0:05:28.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I became a housekeeper here through Misa's introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:30.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:37.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa was a really nice girl, always attentive and kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:39.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:41.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does a person like that have to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:45.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just maybe... it could be because of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:52.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa's father, Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, came home from the hospital for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:56.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He grabbed his wife, Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and was very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.25,0:06:01.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "You really deceived me for the past 20 years!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:04.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Deceived him? About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.38,0:06:08.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have no idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:11.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when Misa got badly hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:12.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Badly hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:14.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:18.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa went between them to stop the fight, but Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} pushed her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:22.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She hit her head on a pillar, and had to have seven stitches in her forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:28.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa became gloomy, and rested from work at the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.49,0:06:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,until she met Robert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.70,0:06:32.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Robert?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.16,0:06:32.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.87,0:06:37.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The day of a landslide three years ago, Misa happened on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:42.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was caught in a landslide while taking pictures, and was badly hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:47.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, the hospital rooms were full that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.21,0:06:50.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa had no choice, so she had him treated at the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:53.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and brought him here and took care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.14,0:06:56.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the beginning, she had a hard time taking care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.47,0:06:58.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The inside of Robert's mouth was cut up from the landslide,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.14,0:07:00.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he couldn't speak well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:07.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Robert could speak Japanese, but it seems he couldn't read or write it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:11.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the conversation with Misa took place on paper with Roman letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.66,0:07:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when Robert got better and was able to talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they seemed to be enjoying things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They told all sorts of jokes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:23.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Japanese foods are delicious, especially on rainy days,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.29,0:07:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,dirt and{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} san{\r}d are excellent"{o.O?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.75,0:07:31.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm a prince of a certain country, and I came to find a bride who is like light"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.30,0:07:35.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the time Robert's wounds had healed and a farewell party was to be held,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:40.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and his family were home, and he became friends with them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.14,0:07:42.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa also became bright again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.98,0:07:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that makes it more confusing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:52.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it two or three days after Robert went home that Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:53.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:56.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but after Robert went home, Misa became gloomy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:02.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She suddenly disappeared, and everyone thought she ran away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:07.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yūzō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the one who found Misa dead on the second floor of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.38,0:08:11.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And several days later,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.97,0:08:18.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,her mother, Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, also committed suicide in the warehouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.26,0:08:22.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After the two died, was there anybody who had a{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge in attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.77,0:08:24.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:30.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came to the funeral without tears or sad expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.28,0:08:32.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but on the other hand, Ryūji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one who was a big problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:38.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He cried in a voice so loud it echoed throughout the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.28,0:08:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The others would be Sae{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Emi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:44.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, those twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:49.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of them were such good friends with Robert,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:52.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but two years ago, when they came back to visit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.55,0:08:54.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they suddenly started saying something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.26,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It was Robert...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:00.72,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Robert is the one who killed Misa-{\i1}neechan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:01.93,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Isn't it terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.93,0:09:03.14,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Terrible, terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.23,0:09:08.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the children say something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.19,0:09:09.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:13.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who came to pick up the dolls, was also surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.78,0:09:18.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because after they talked to him, they suddenly started saying those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:19.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did they talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.95,0:09:21.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.20,0:09:24.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said they only asked him his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.83,0:09:30.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who died in the shed the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.59,0:09:35.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was out to attend to the neighborhood gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.01,0:09:40.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came home ahead of the others to prepare dinner and found him in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.26,0:09:43.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you around then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.06,0:09:48.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was with Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, buying groceries at the supermarket for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.10,0:09:49.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.52,0:09:50.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.06,0:09:55.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After his wife died, Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took over the household finances.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.41,0:10:03.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, the rope used to hang Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and the string around him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:05.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,can they be found in this warehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:07.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, for the string...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:11.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a lot of it because it's used to make the marionettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.75,0:10:16.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The ropes are in the shed. Would you like to go and see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.68,0:10:20.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Gee, it's raining hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.14,0:10:25.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudō, do you know who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:29.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope... Not who the killer is, or the locked room trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a single lead...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:33.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left the living room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:36.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Robert went to the shed to get the car, and left with Ran and Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:40.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't go near the warehouse even once. It couldn't be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:43.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was in the bath with the twins,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:46.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the housekeeper who was cleaning up in the living room with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.79,0:10:50.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the old lady who was in her room, are also clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.00,0:10:50.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.63,0:10:57.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who could have done anything are Ryūji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the one making the bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:11:01.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Yūzō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was looking all over the house for Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.39,0:11:04.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But something bugs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.97,0:11:06.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:10.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The string, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:12.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:16.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the killer have to use the string to make it look like a curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:18.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.53,0:11:23.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he didn't do that, we would have thought it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.95,0:11:28.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that request letter that was sent to you also bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:29.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.20,0:11:31.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was sent by the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:34.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he taking me lightly and challenging me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:40.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something fishy about this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:44.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, the rope...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.05,0:11:47.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is somebody there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.39,0:11:50.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.02,0:11:55.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Kazuha's missing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:56.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.06,0:11:59.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Only her penlight was on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.78,0:12:03.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought someone carried her off and panicked...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:06.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's split up and look for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.62,0:12:11.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha! Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:12.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.83,0:12:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:18.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, have you found her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.13,0:12:19.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... She's nowhere to be seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:28.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Hattori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.14,0:12:30.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The door to the warehouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.89,0:12:32.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I closed it, but it's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.07,0:12:42.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:43.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:47.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:12:55.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.79,0:12:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hang in there, Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:59.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha! Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:01.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.42,0:13:03.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:05.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.97,0:13:10.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What... happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.93,0:13:14.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember... waiting for Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} in front of the warehouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly felt faint...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:19.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet! I'll cut you loose right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:22.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:25.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you were just hanging with the strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:28.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I'm so sorry, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.62,0:13:32.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't search hard enough, and got you into this terrible situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.79,0:13:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... The mascot...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.91,0:13:36.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... I found it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:39.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was caught on the lid of my CD player.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:42.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry... If I'd taken a closer look...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.63,0:13:46.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you found it. Don't lose it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.51,0:13:52.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hattori...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:54.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.06,0:13:56.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, please take care of Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.31,0:13:58.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.48,0:14:00.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:04.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer tried to use our blind spot by hanging Kazuha up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.11,0:14:07.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in the warehouse we were in a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:12.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After leaving, the killer brought Kazuha here, and wrapped her in the strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.58,0:14:14.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then all that remained was to put that rope around her neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:16.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the curse would be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.37,0:14:20.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one reason the killer had to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.21,0:14:25.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer noticed my footsteps when I ran over here, and left in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.46,0:14:32.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the killer is still here, in the warehouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.10,0:14:40.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudō. Are my deductions wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:43.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.82,0:14:48.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's take a look at the killer's face!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:56.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is he around?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.04,0:14:57.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:02.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. It hasn't been 3 minutes since we came to this warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:06.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were guarding the entrance on the first floor, so there's nowhere to hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:10.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only place to escape would be that tiny window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.97,0:15:12.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.97,0:15:16.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a way to get out through there in such a short time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.02,0:15:21.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time that girl from Osaka was attacked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-By who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:25.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.94,0:15:31.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha is resting in the room right now, but she may remember in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:33.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...one of the faces among you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:38.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One reason we had you gather here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:41.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was to prevent any more murders from taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.16,0:15:45.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The other was to confirm your alibis!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.21,0:15:50.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alibis? We were asleep in our rooms all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.34,0:15:51.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.72,0:15:56.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in my room too, but I wasn't asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.22,0:16:00.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you? I didn't see you when we were searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.98,0:16:03.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was searching outside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:07.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, nobody has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:08.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.23,0:16:12.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yūzō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s not around...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:15.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yūzō? Wouldn't he be in the workshop?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.24,0:16:19.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was here working the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:27.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was putting the finishing touches on the doll Brother had to complete by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:31.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can make dolls too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.09,0:16:35.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago, my company went bankrupt, and I came back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:44.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother taught me all sorts of things and let me do the simple constructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.39,0:16:47.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago... That's the time of that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:52.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I came home just after Robert left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:58.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wasn't allowed to make fixtures{?} or do repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.57,0:17:05.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother's marionettes cost ¥1,000,000 apiece, and he charged ¥700,000 for repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:08.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He sold them for ¥1,000,000 and repaired them for ¥700,000?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:11.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can he do business like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.21,0:17:12.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:17.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like there are some people who request repairs more than ten times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.14,0:17:21.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He charged quite a bit for the marionettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.39,0:17:28.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With the money he made, he often went abroad with Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:36.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After leaving the sales to Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the dolls began to command high prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's that big doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:45.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's the marionette of the "spider empress".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:52.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Father was alive, dolls of that size were used at every festival
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:55.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to do plays of the "spider empress".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:18:00.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the number of people able to handle dolls that big gradually disappeared{oi, oi.},
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.01,0:18:01.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and they quit doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:04.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those boxes that are stacked up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.31,0:18:10.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, those are the dolls that Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was supposed to take that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.65,0:18:16.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, Brother realized he was one doll short.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.53,0:18:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The customer called directly and he had to make one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.99,0:18:26.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:29.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,please stay in the room everyone is gathered in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:31.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to be by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.88,0:18:32.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:36.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, now's our{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The repair fees for the dolls are extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.68,0:18:44.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the price, there are customers who request repairs more than 10 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.72,0:18:49.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A simple puppet that's expensive means
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:50.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,what's inside is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.81,0:18:52.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,narcotics!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:56.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the marionettes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.99,0:19:03.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you can only put the narcotics in the head, so the price is cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.37,0:19:05.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.20,0:19:08.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know why Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called a detective
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.33,0:19:10.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to find out who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:14.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A large part of the entire picture has come into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.67,0:19:18.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's left that we don't know is the locked room trick
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.84,0:19:22.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and why Kazuha was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.34,0:19:25.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sae? Emi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.60,0:19:27.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.93,0:19:30.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The two daughters I brought to the restroom aren't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:31.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.23,0:19:33.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mother...\N- Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:38.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You worried me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:41.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you to wait in front of the restroom when you were through?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.49,0:19:43.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.61,0:19:45.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There sure was! A funny smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.91,0:19:48.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably the spider children burning in the furnace!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.54,0:19:50.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:51.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandmother said so, didn't she...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:53.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She did! She did!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.50,0:19:54.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Furnace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:04.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, there's something strange burning in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.14,0:20:07.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come to think of it... What was the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.06,0:20:11.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it, didn't you? You called Robert "murderer"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.98,0:20:13.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The day Robert was leaving,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.64,0:20:16.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Misa-{\i1}neechan{\i0} told us to go and ask him what his feelings were,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:19.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we went to the bus stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:23.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We asked him, "How do you feel about Misa-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:26.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Robert wrote a terrible thing down on paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.41,0:20:27.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Didn't he?\N- Didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:28.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrible thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.99,0:20:30.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- He wrote, "die!"\N- He wrote, "die!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.79,0:20:31.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Die?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:32.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:34.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrible, terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.83,0:20:36.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.17,0:20:39.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The children probably saw wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.17,0:20:42.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't have shown that name card.{...business card, prolly?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:43.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Name card?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.67,0:20:46.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, I'm sure I have it here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.35,0:20:59.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They found this name card inside the wallet and made a lot of noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.02,0:21:02.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They asked, "Who did you get this from?" "Where is this person?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.15,0:21:04.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.16,0:21:08.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it out somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:10.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.16,0:21:10.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.12,0:21:14.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a stun gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:17.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:20.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Heiji! I feel much better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take off your clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.05,0:21:24.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just let me see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.34,0:21:26.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.34,0:21:27.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.39,0:21:32.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I the only one to get hit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:34.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:37.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.35,0:21:40.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Small burn marks on her back...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.31,0:21:43.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she {\i1}was{\i0} knocked out with a stun gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.23,0:21:46.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And? Did she say anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.36,0:21:47.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't see the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.95,0:21:50.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but she said she found a strange ball in front of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.74,0:21:51.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.20,0:21:54.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She said it was a ball about this small.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.66,0:21:56.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}BB shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.17,0:21:59.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.25,0:22:01.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I never thought of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.09,0:22:02.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If that's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.63,0:22:04.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:05.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Should be somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.92,0:22:07.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.55,0:22:11.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it! Hattori, it's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.14,0:22:13.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The marks of a thumbtack!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.10,0:22:14.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.39,0:22:18.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange string with loops on the beam ends!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:21.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as we thought, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.65,0:22:23.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.11,0:22:29.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no mistake... That person is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.32,0:00:14.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.32,0:00:14.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[NEP]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.16,0:24:03.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer didn't need to escape from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.33,0:24:07.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.29,0:24:13.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was to avenge Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who committed suicide in this warehouse three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.55,0:24:16.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.01,0:24:21.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one person who could have done it without anyone noticing!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.39,0:24:23.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.06,0:24:28.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[Mystery of the Spider House of Tottori (Case Closed)]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:33.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Romaji
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.66,0:24:36.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, the solution at last!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:38.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, it'll be the killer who gets caught in the web!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.53,0:24:39.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
